1
00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:23,260
♪Wandering alone♪

2
00:00:23,260 --> 00:00:25,540
♪Walking far by dusk-lit streets♪

3
00:00:25,540 --> 00:00:27,430
♪Your eyes are as cold as clouds♪

4
00:00:27,430 --> 00:00:28,970
♪Faintly coming into view♪

5
00:00:28,970 --> 00:00:30,360
♪The city lights♪

6
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:32,630
♪Lit up that single moment♪

7
00:00:32,630 --> 00:00:36,140
♪I can't hide or stop missing you♪

8
00:00:36,140 --> 00:00:37,640
♪I can't forget those moments♪

9
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:39,280
♪Losing you♪

10
00:00:39,610 --> 00:00:41,320
♪Like the seasons in my memory♪

11
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:43,290
♪Without winter♪

12
00:00:43,290 --> 00:00:44,920
♪Walking down the long, dark street♪

13
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:46,460
♪Snow will never fall again♪

14
00:00:46,460 --> 00:00:48,200
♪Our old story was torn♪

15
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:50,610
♪Into scattered pieces♪

16
00:00:50,610 --> 00:00:53,430
♪Replaying every single scene♪

17
00:00:53,430 --> 00:00:55,980
♪After you left♪

18
00:00:57,530 --> 00:01:00,510
♪As if our documentary♪

19
00:01:00,510 --> 00:01:03,120
♪Lost winter♪

20
00:01:04,770 --> 00:01:07,180
♪The breeze speaks of good times♪

21
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:11,080
♪Pure white devotion♪

22
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:13,990
♪Send out a letter♪

23
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:17,780
♪Carrying my longing♪

24
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:20,980
=The Double Game=

25
00:01:21,020 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 18=

26
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:49,140
(Lu Tingxiao's uncle, Fang Wenyuan)

27
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:49,990
Uncle, don't worry.

28
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:51,760
It's safe here.

29
00:01:57,070 --> 00:01:58,120
Can you tell me

30
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:01,040
why Lu Jianchuan locked you up

31
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:04,150
for so many years?

32
00:02:04,710 --> 00:02:05,550
Why?

33
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:09,520
He feared I'd expose his secrets

34
00:02:09,910 --> 00:02:11,000
and ruin everything he had.

35
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:16,470
I...

36
00:02:17,030 --> 00:02:18,560
once saw

37
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,430
a certification document.

38
00:02:21,590 --> 00:02:23,000
It had my mom's signature on it.

39
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,120
He must've used that document

40
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,630
to get the project approved.

41
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:31,120
It was approved by my grandpa.

42
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,590
What exactly happened?

43
00:02:36,710 --> 00:02:39,000
Your mom was too innocent back then.

44
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,150
Meeting Lu Jianchuan

45
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:44,120
was the start of her tragedy.

46
00:02:44,743 --> 00:02:46,633
At the time,
your grandpa was still in office.

47
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:47,960
Your mom

48
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:50,470
was fooled
by Lu Jianchuan's fake kindness

49
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:51,710
and care.

50
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:53,086
She insisted on marrying him.

51
00:02:54,310 --> 00:02:55,190
Later,

52
00:02:55,479 --> 00:02:56,938
she even used our family's resources

53
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:57,910
with his startup.

54
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,470
Until Lu Jianchuan

55
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:01,520
used the Lianxin Island project

56
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:03,630
to completely destroy our family.

57
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,750
Lu Jianchuan used those dirty tricks

58
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,870
to get the development permit.

59
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:19,120
After that, he got even bolder.

60
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,400
He used the signatures and approval

61
00:03:22,580 --> 00:03:23,450
to force your mother

62
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:25,030
to keep taking money from our family.

63
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:27,360
After your grandpa found out,

64
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,360
he had a heart attack

65
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:31,920
and died suddenly.

66
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:37,710
Your mom was already torn up inside.

67
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,680
When Lu saw she'd lost support,

68
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:42,310
he actually got back together

69
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:43,870
with his old flame.

70
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:45,800
Later, he even brought her home.

71
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:47,960
Your mom couldn't take

72
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,240
that many blows anymore.

73
00:03:50,310 --> 00:03:51,150
In the end...

74
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,120
I couldn't let it go

75
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,190
and went to settle things with Lu.

76
00:04:00,590 --> 00:04:02,680
I said I'd expose all his dirty secrets.

77
00:04:02,870 --> 00:04:04,150
I never thought he'd be so low

78
00:04:04,710 --> 00:04:06,030
as to lock me up.

79
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,560
That ordeal

80
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:10,710
lasted more than ten years.

81
00:04:28,390 --> 00:04:29,296
How's your uncle doing?

82
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,440
Is he asleep?

83
00:04:33,390 --> 00:04:35,600
You don't look well.

84
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,480
Did you find any leads?

85
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,360
Nothing important.

86
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:50,510
It's okay if you don't want to say.

87
00:04:54,310 --> 00:04:55,150
Wen Yan,

88
00:04:56,950 --> 00:04:58,600
if the price of the truth

89
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:01,920
is the person you love most

90
00:05:02,430 --> 00:05:03,390
losing everything,

91
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:07,120
would you still keep going?

92
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,390
I understand your struggle

93
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:14,600
and why you want to protect your uncle.

94
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:16,950
The truth matters,

95
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,520
but people

96
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:20,880
matter too.

97
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:24,630
It's not my uncle.

98
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,720
It's my mom.

99
00:05:32,950 --> 00:05:34,240
She was used by Lu Jianchuan.

100
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,920
Without even knowing it,

101
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,560
she signed forged documents.

102
00:05:41,310 --> 00:05:42,390
Also, my grandpa

103
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:45,390
was fooled

104
00:05:46,390 --> 00:05:47,430
by Lu Jianchuan's schemes.

105
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,766
It left a stain on his career.

106
00:05:49,986 --> 00:05:51,879
Once the truth
about Lianxin Island comes out,

107
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,680
they'll lose everything.

108
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,480
No matter what you choose,

109
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,120
I'll support you.

110
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:06,030
You need to know

111
00:06:07,070 --> 00:06:08,160
you're not alone.

112
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:12,830
I'll stay with you.

113
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:36,150
Where is he?

114
00:06:39,070 --> 00:06:40,120
Who let him go?

115
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:42,590
Tell me.

116
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:48,590
You...

117
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,310
You betrayed me too.

118
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,560
You betrayed me first.

119
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,800
You wanted to climb higher,

120
00:06:59,510 --> 00:07:01,160
so you threw our love away.

121
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:04,190
When you joined the Fang family,

122
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:06,800
why not stay loyal?

123
00:07:07,190 --> 00:07:09,630
I had my reasons back then.

124
00:07:10,390 --> 00:07:12,190
I was thinking about our future.

125
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:13,880
Do you really

126
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,040
want a hard life in the countryside?

127
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:19,630
If I hadn't endured all that,

128
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,480
would we live this well now?

129
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,240
Then what about Lin Yuqing now?

130
00:07:24,190 --> 00:07:25,120
What humiliation

131
00:07:25,510 --> 00:07:26,350
are you enduring?

132
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,240
I don't want to argue about this.

133
00:07:31,270 --> 00:07:32,310
Don't think

134
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,160
letting them out can scare me.

135
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,360
I'm telling you.

136
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:39,960
I only

137
00:07:40,510 --> 00:07:42,040
kept them locked up for a while.

138
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:43,270
I didn't kill anyone.

139
00:07:43,870 --> 00:07:45,000
Even if they get out,

140
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:46,390
what can they do to me?

141
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,830
Those young punks alone

142
00:07:53,430 --> 00:07:54,510
can't shake things up.

143
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,120
(Put myself in his shoes.)

144
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,600
(If my mom were mixed up in this,)

145
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,920
(I'd probably be hurting like he is.)

146
00:08:15,070 --> 00:08:17,000
(But where is my mom?)

147
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,720
(Is she doing okay?)

148
00:08:27,430 --> 00:08:28,270
Her name is Wen Hui.

149
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:30,720
Her household registration record
is active.

150
00:08:48,420 --> 00:08:51,300
(Wen Hui)

151
00:08:56,550 --> 00:08:57,910
I'll cook for you.

152
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:02,440
Here, have some fruit.

153
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:07,220
(Wen Hui)

154
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:11,200
(I've searched and wondered)

155
00:09:12,270 --> 00:09:13,630
(for so long.)

156
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,110
(Mom,)

157
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:19,750
(you've been by my side all along.)

158
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:36,180
(Love Is Timeless like Pearls.
Pearl Bay)

159
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,270
Let's go inside first.

160
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,440
In the depths of the sea,

161
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:08,600
there was a beautiful Pearl Bay,

162
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:12,240
where a kind Mermaid Princess lived.

163
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:14,110
One day,

164
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:15,720
the Mermaid Princess

165
00:10:15,870 --> 00:10:17,720
saved a merchant from a wreck.

166
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,550
The merchant was charming and witty.

167
00:10:20,939 --> 00:10:22,072
He told the Mermaid Princess

168
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:24,720
of the vast, vibrant world above.

169
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,960
She soon fell in love with him

170
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:30,080
and brought him back to Pearl Bay.

171
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,670
The merchant told the Merfolk King

172
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:36,120
he could take the pearls of Pearl Bay

173
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,390
to the land above

174
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:40,030
so more people could see their beauty

175
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,720
and, in turn, bring Pearl Bay

176
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:45,080
endless wealth and honor.

177
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:50,270
Blinded by love and his lies,

178
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:53,270
the Princess
persuaded her loving father.

179
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:54,960
However,

180
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,600
once the merchant got the pearls,

181
00:10:58,270 --> 00:11:00,000
he showed his true colors at once.

182
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,600
He was never a stranded traveler.

183
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,840
He was a hunter all along.

184
00:11:06,270 --> 00:11:08,630
He teamed up with a greedy lord.

185
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:11,600
They stole Pearl Bay's pearls in bulk

186
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:14,750
and cast aside
the pregnant Mermaid Princess.

187
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:16,800
As it turned out,

188
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,550
the merchant already had

189
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:20,200
a family on the land.

190
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,000
When the old King learned the truth,

191
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:24,750
he was crushed by rage

192
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,120
and fell sick.

193
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:29,200
Pearl Bay lost its pearls

194
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:31,510
and all its former joy,

195
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,360
and slowly faded away.

196
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:37,000
As for that greedy lord and hunter,

197
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:38,790
they feared the merfolk's revenge,

198
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,510
so they sent their men

199
00:11:40,910 --> 00:11:43,030
to snatch away
the newborn little mermaid,

200
00:11:44,630 --> 00:11:46,120
but what they didn't know was

201
00:11:46,670 --> 00:11:49,720
that Mermaid Princess had two daughters.

202
00:11:51,390 --> 00:11:53,910
To keep her younger girl safe,

203
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:55,720
Mermaid Princess

204
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,870
tearfully sent her away to be raised.

205
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:01,600
From afar, Mermaid Princess

206
00:12:01,790 --> 00:12:03,960
quietly watched both girls grow up.

207
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:05,800
She thought

208
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:08,390
once her older daughter
married the lord's son,

209
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:10,550
she'd live in peace.

210
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:11,920
But unexpectedly,

211
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:14,390
she still suffered so much hurt.

212
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:17,240
Her younger daughter suffered too.

213
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:21,360
Mermaid Princess's biggest regret

214
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,390
was failing to protect them

215
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:26,720
and stay by their side as they grew.

216
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:42,910
Mom.

217
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,320
Yan.

218
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:48,790
My daughter.

219
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,200
Mom.

220
00:12:55,030 --> 00:12:55,960
Zhi'er.

221
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,750
Zhi'er.

222
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,840
My precious daughter.

223
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:10,840
Mom.

224
00:13:12,620 --> 00:13:17,220
(Our story began with Pearl Bay's tide)

225
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,040
Congratulations.

226
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:37,706
You finally found your family.

227
00:13:38,209 --> 00:13:40,095
You're not
the lonely little elephant anymore.

228
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,040
Tingxiao,

229
00:13:46,630 --> 00:13:48,120
you're not alone anymore either.

230
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,510
I'm your family too.

231
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,850
♪This door♪

232
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:44,000
♪Lets in the sky outside♪

233
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:48,040
♪With a voice even lighter♪

234
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:50,850
♪Than how you just greeted me♪

235
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:52,670
♪I know now♪

236
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:57,880
♪What the chill in my body means♪

237
00:14:58,230 --> 00:15:01,100
♪The moment salt hits the wound♪

238
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:04,720
♪My heart still beats so naively♪

239
00:15:04,890 --> 00:15:07,880
♪To complete♪

240
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:12,090
♪A joy that needs no brave pretense♪

241
00:15:12,230 --> 00:15:14,730
♪How cruel sincerity can be♪

242
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:18,420
♪Like a door with no key♪

243
00:15:18,730 --> 00:15:21,050
♪Maybe you just passed by♪

244
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:24,630
♪The tears in my eyes♪

245
00:15:25,340 --> 00:15:27,890
♪You looked like you had nothing to say♪

246
00:15:27,890 --> 00:15:29,630
♪Then got so good at being cold♪

247
00:15:29,630 --> 00:15:32,470
♪That's why a smile feels so precious♪

248
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:34,770
♪Maybe you just passed by♪

249
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:39,250
♪The tears burned into my heart♪

250
00:15:39,630 --> 00:15:41,920
♪Let's say silence was just for show♪

251
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:46,590
♪Even if I've grown another year♪
